sql:
SELECT store_id, name
FROM stores
ORDER BY open_date ASC;

SELECT name, open_date
FROM stores
ORDER BY open_date ASC;

SELECT
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users) AS Total_Users,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM products) AS Total_Products;

external_knowledge:
- "shops" refers to "stores";
- "electronic gadgets" refers to products in the 'Electronics' category;
- "newest to the oldest based on their opening dates" means ordering by the 'open_date' column in descending order.
